  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "1 Adult Serving = 2 Kids Servings\nPeel and finely grate the ginger. Peel and coarsely grate the carrot. Finely chop the garlic. Trim and finely slice the spring onions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the ginger, carrot, garlic, spring onions, pork mince, soy sauce, honey, cornflour, a pinch of salt and some black pepper to a large bowl. Use your hands to mix everything together until well combined."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Shape the mixture into small patties — about the size of a golf ball, then flatten slightly."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a drizzle of sunflower oil in a large non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. Fry the patties in batches for 3–4 mins on each side until golden brown and cooked through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "If making the spring onion oil for the adults, finely slice the remaining spring onions and pop them into a heatproof bowl. Heat the sunflower oil in a small pan until just smoking, then carefully pour over the spring onions. Let it sit for a few mins to mellow. \nSlice the chilli."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve up!\nKids Plate: Serve the patties however your kids like. We've gone with sliced cucumber and cooked jasmine rice.\nParents Plate: Top the patties on the rice, add a drizzle of soy sauce, spring onion oil, a scattering of chopped chilli, coriander and a squeeze of lime."
    }
  ],
  "tips": [
    "These freeze brilliantly. Let them cool, then freeze in a single layer before transferring to a container. (They'll keep for 3 months in the freezer)",
    "You can reheat from frozen in the oven or pan until piping hot.",
    "Great for lunchboxes too — pop into wraps or rice bowls. (They keep for up to 3 days in the fridge)"
  ],
